wiki.summary: In “Safaera” the mythical Ñengo Flow and Jowell Y Randy reunite, who together make a trip through time going through different eras, grouping classic reggaeton sounds, including a hard dembow, through different rhythmic changes. Different samples and references to iconic songs are made, some of the genre, like “El Tiburón”, and others not, like “Get Ur Freak On”. This experimental song talks about partying and a lot of dirty perreo, with a high sexual content and also various references to drugs. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: In “Safaera” the mythical Ñengo Flow and Jowell Y Randy reunite, who together make a trip through time going through different eras, grouping classic reggaeton sounds, including a hard dembow, through different rhythmic changes. Different samples and references to iconic songs are made, some of the genre, like “El Tiburón”, and others not, like “Get Ur Freak On”. This experimental song talks about partying and a lot of dirty perreo, with a high sexual content and also various references to drugs. Since his departure, his popularity has increased until he has a strong recognition in social networks at an international level. It was in high positions on the Billboard and Spotify charts.
